        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-06-03 15:56:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n> > \n> > Is Policy Audit in the TOSCA Spec?\n> \n> The audit is to register when policy deploy/undeploy is requested from PAP. the Tosca Identifier is referred (name/version). Let me know if this is enough to answer your question or if you need further info.\n\nHi Pam, not sure if we have some audit related entities in Tosca spec. But this feature we are building is to allow PF users to know basic details of \"what happened when\" with an initial target to support deploy, undeploy, create & delete operations. This is really beneficial in cases where the PDP engines are shared across multiple use cases. Also, gives more transparency of the operations taken internally by PAP due to some mismatch or failures in PDPs.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
